Date:  0/0/1843
Source:  TrNZi
Author:  DiEFFENBACH
Vol / Page:  1/318
Edition:
Quote:  The kahikatea bears very numerous seeds in bunches: the fruit is double; ... both parts are of the size of pepper-corns. According to the natives, these berries, which they call koroi, ripen only every third year.
Notes:

